Troubleshooting Tips
API Rate Limiting Issues:

Free Shodan accounts have query limits (typically 100 queries/month)
Implement time.sleep(1) between queries to avoid rate limiting
Use --limit parameter to reduce results per query
Check remaining credits with shodan info
Import Errors:

Ensure all required libraries are installed: pip3 install shodan pandas matplotlib openpyxl
Use python3 instead of python on Linux systems
Verify Python version is 3.6 or higher: python3 --version
Empty Results:

Verify API key is correctly configured: shodan info
Check internet connectivity and firewall settings
Ensure search queries are properly formatted
Try simpler queries first (e.g., just "apache")
Permission Errors:

Make scripts executable: chmod +x script_name.py
Ensure write permissions in working directory
Run with appropriate user privileges (avoid unnecessary sudo)
